author: Mao Taketani
Shuyi Zhang
Timothy Jones
media: TYG (10 g/L Tryptone Peptone, 5 g/L Yeast Extract, 11 mM Glucose, 100 mM KPO4 (pH7.2), 72µM CaCl2, 0.4 µg/ml FeSO4 and 1µg/mL Resazurin, 1.2 µg/ml hematin, 0.5g/mL of L-cysteine, and 1 µg/ml of Vitamin K (menadione)
growth: Inoculation: Inoculate individual colonies into TYG media without antibiotics and grow 18 hours overnight in the anaerobic chamber.  Dilution and Induction: Next day, dilute 100-fold into pre-reduced TYG with inducers (no antibiotics), grow for 6 hours in the anaerobic chamber.  Measurement: Plate Reader, data processing for RPUL normalization.

normalization_instructions: The following equation converts the average Nanoluc luminescence (RLU/CFU) to RPUL.  RPUL = (NL)/(NLRPU), where NL is the average luminescence RLU/CFU of the cells of interest and NLRPU is the average luminescence RLU/CFU of the cells containing the RPU standard.
plasmid_description:
pNBU1 plasmid backbone with ampicillin resistance for selection in E.coli and erythromycin resistance for selection in B.theta. A Nanoluc expression cassette. Upstream isulation by terminator tL17
and a 5’-BsaI site.  Promoter PAM3, ribozyme RiboJ, RBS rpiL* drives constitutive Nanoluc expression, with transcriptional termination by L3S2P21.
